{
  "body": "Luxurious cinematic social-media editorial portrait — {{subject}}.\n\n— Pose & wardrobe —\n{{subject}} {{pose}}, wearing {{attire}}. Confident expression, slightly distant editorial gaze (not smiling pleasantly — sophisticated and slightly aloof). The body language reads as effortless premium creator, not posed mannequin.\n\n— Background & environment —\n{{background}}. The floor is soft, smooth, slightly glossy, with a faint mirror reflection of the subject and the floating elements above.\n\n— Floating digital elements (the visual signature of this image) —\nAround the subject, suspended in the air at varying depths and orientations, distribute the following floating elements with cinematic depth-of-field separation:\n\n  • Floating logos: {{floating_brand_logos}}. Sized at varying scales — some closer to the camera (slightly out of focus, larger), some farther back (sharper, smaller). Tilted at different angles, NOT all facing camera. They have a 3D physical presence with subtle shadow contact, NOT flat 2D stickers.\n\n  • Floating content: {{floating_content_cards}}. Glassmorphism style — semi-transparent white frosted glass with very subtle blur of background visible through them, soft 1–2px white border, gentle drop shadow. Tilted in 3D space, not flat to camera.\n\nThese floating elements are arranged in a controlled, considered constellation around the subject — NOT a chaotic snowstorm. Some elements are slightly occluded by the subject's hair, blazer edge, or hand, creating real spatial depth. The total count of floating items: roughly 5–9 logos + 3–5 content cards.\n\n— Color discipline (CRITICAL) —\nEntire image follows {{monochrome_scheme}}. Subject's clothing, the floor, the background, the floating cards — all stay within this single hue family. The only allowed accent: the floating logos may use their authentic brand color (e.g., red YouTube triangle, pink/cyan TikTok outline) but kept restrained and small. Otherwise: no rainbow, no bright pop colors, no neon competing with the subject.\n\n— Lighting —\n{{lighting_style}}. Light wraps softly around the subject, casts a delicate dreamy shadow on the floor, and creates faint catchlights on the glass surface of the floating cards.\n\n— Skin & material rendering —\n{{skin_finish}}. Hair has individual highlighted strands, fabric has visible weave texture and subtle wrinkles, glass cards have authentic frosted refraction.\n\n— Composition —\nHigh-end editorial magazine layout. Subject occupies the visual center / golden ratio sweet spot. Floating elements form a balanced halo around but never overpower the subject. Captured in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio with cinematic depth-of-field — subject sharp, floating elements with selective focus (some sharp, some softly blurred).\n\n— Style references —\nFuturistic influencer aesthetic. Luxury creator-brand campaign. High-end editorial fashion photography. Reference visual mood: a Solange Vogue Italia editorial, an early-2020s Off-White lookbook, and a contemporary Apple Vision Pro keynote visual — all merged. \"Viral AI art\" polish but anchored in real fashion photography discipline.\n\n— Additional details —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid —\n- Do NOT use bright pop colors that break the {{monochrome_scheme}} (except small logo brand colors)\n- Do NOT make the floating elements a chaotic storm — they must be a curated constellation\n- Do NOT render floating elements as flat 2D stickers — they have 3D presence with light interaction\n- Do NOT over-smooth the skin into plastic doll — preserve subsurface texture\n- Do NOT generate gibberish text on the floating cards — if uncertain about specific characters, use abstract bars or simplified placeholders rather than fake glyphs\n- Do NOT add lens flares, sun rays, particle dust effects competing with the subject\n- Do NOT make the subject smile broadly — keep the expression sophisticated and editorial\n- Do NOT render in cartoon, anime, or stylized illustration mode — this is photoreal CGI editorial photography\n- Do NOT add product placement (Coke cans, branded coffee cups) unless extra_notes specifies\n- Do NOT add any watermarks, mockup frames, or stock-illustration trademarks\n- Do NOT clutter the background with props (plants, books, frames) — keep the minimal vibe\n\n— Output —\nUltra-detailed 8K resolution, photoreal CGI editorial photography quality, print-ready. Indistinguishable from a real high-fashion magazine cover shoot enhanced with subtle CGI floating elements.\n\nKeywords: editorial portrait, futuristic influencer, creator brand, glassmorphism, monochrome fashion, soft studio light, dreamy shadows, viral AI art, hyper-real skin, cinematic depth, luxury creator, Apple keynote aesthetic",
